            <entry xml:id="entry_æng0yrstwan" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d4230e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æng˳yrstwan</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d4230e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ængurstewan</orth><form xml:id="form_d4230e71" type="variant"><orth>ængurstewnæ</orth></form><form xml:id="form_d4230e73" type="variant"><orth>ængurstawnæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d4230e76"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>наперсток</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>thimble</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d4230e86">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4230e88">
                        <quote>Sajnæg-ældary ḱyzg kærdgæ-xujgæ kæny, jæ sūʒīn æmæ je ʽng˳yrstwan
                            tævd kænync, īxǵyn don jæ cūry dary, æmæ sæ ūcy ran tūly</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дочь Сайнаг-алдара кроит-шьет, ее игла и наперсток накаляются, она
                                держит возле себя ледяную воду и туда их погружает</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Sajnag-aldar’s daughter is cutting-sewing, her niddle and thimble are
                                becoming hot, she has ice-cold water near her and she is dipping
                                them there</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            98</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4230e107">
                        <quote>konǧædæ æ soʒīnæ, fæstæ je ʽngurstewæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бревно (служит) ей иглой, ступа — наперстком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a beam serves her as a niddle, a mortar serves as a thimble</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 108</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e168" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e129" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*angušta-pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>покрышка пальца</q></gloss></mentioned> (<hi rendition="#rend_italic">pānа</hi>- от корня
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">pā</hi>- ‘оберегать’, ‘прикрывать’, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnæg"/>),
                    ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e178" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e139" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>anguštpana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e183" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e144" xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštbān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e186" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e147" xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštwāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>наперсток</q></gloss></mentioned>. Наличное в ос. <hi rendition="#rend_italic">r</hi> —
                    результат контаминации с другим вариантом *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">angur</hi>- ‘палец’, наличным в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æng0ylʒ"/> ‘палец’. Возможно заимствование из
                    персидского; но через какое посредство?%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e129" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e168" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*angušta-pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>finger-cover</q></gloss></mentioned> (<hi rendition="#rend_italic">pānа</hi>- is derived from
                    the root <hi rendition="#rend_italic">pā</hi>- ‘to protect’, ‘to cover’, see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnæg"/>), compare <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e139" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e178" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>anguštpana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e144" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e183" xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštbān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4230e147" xml:id="mentioned_d4230e186" xml:lang="fa"><w>anguštwāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>thimble</q></gloss></mentioned>. There is an <hi rendition="#rend_italic">r</hi> in Ossetic
                    because of contamination with the other variant *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">angur</hi>- ‘finger’, which is
                    found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æng0ylʒ"/> ‘finger’. Probably, it is a
                    loan word from Persian, but what language was a mediation part?%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
